<H3> <TI>   Leotard To Visit Troops Deployed on Rwandan Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leotard To Visit Troops Deployed on Rwandan Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2806081494 Paris AFP in English GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2806081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, June 28 (AFP) -- Defense Minister Francois 
Leotard is to leave here late Tuesday [28 June] to tour the 
Rwandan-Zairean border, where France is deploying 2,500 troops 
to protect civilians threatened by the Rwandan ethnic carnage, 
defense ministry officials said. 
  The officials said Leotard would spend the whole of 
Wednesday 
in the area and would be accompanied by the junior minister for 
humanitarian action, Lucette Michaux-Chevry, or junior Health 
Minister Philippe Douste-Blazy. 

</TEXT>

