<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vatican Official Meets Iraqi's Tariq 'Aziz </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vatican Official Meets Iraqi's Tariq 'Aziz </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2706201794 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1924 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2706201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Vatican, 27 Jun (INA) -- Deputy Prime Minister 
Tariq 'Aziz met here today with Cardinal Sodano, the Vatican 
secretary of state. During the meeting, they discussed the good 
relations between Iraq and the Vatican. The deputy prime 
minister explained Iraq's position on the implementation of the 
Security Council resolutions and the effects of the continued 
unjust blockade against the Iraqi people. 
  'Aziz asserted that the legal and sound implementation of 
Security Council resolutions requires the immediate, 
unconditional lifting of this blockade. 
  Cardinal Sodano noted his understanding of Iraq's position. 
He also reiterated the stand of the Vatican and His Holiness 
the Pope in rejecting the blockade. He also expressed his 
sympathy with the suffering of the Iraqi people as a result of 
this blockade. 
  The deputy prime minister will meet with Pope John Paul II 
tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

