  [Text] On his arrival at Madrid's Barajas Airport today 
from China, Juan Manuel Eguiagaray, minister of industry and 
energy, said it was very important that the presence of Spanish 
industrial interests should be increasingly obvious in a market 
of 1 billion people, as in the People's Republic of China. 
