<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Rebuffs Opposition Criticism of EU Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Rebuffs Opposition Criticism of EU Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706164694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2706164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos attributed 
the opposition parties' criticism of the government for the 
results of the EU [European Union] summit on Corfu to cowardice 
and ignorance. The opposition parties' criticism of the Greek 
presidency and the results of the EU summit, Venizelos said, is 
a reflection of party cowardice, ignorance, party demagoguery, 
as well as international developments. The public has seen and 
can judge for itself, Venizelos said. He added that being in 
opposition does not mean criticizing the government to win 
points. The opposition, he concluded, is not a simple contract 
which is carried out, but a democratic function. 

</TEXT>

