<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Criticizes PKK Rally in Germany </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Criticizes PKK Rally in Germany </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2706174394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1550 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2706174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 27 (AA) -- Foreign Ministry spokesman 
Ferhat Ataman said on Monday [27 June] that a demonstration of 
the separatist terrorist PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] 
organization held in Frankfurt has turned to a terrorist 
activity. Ataman said the demonstration was a kind of terrorist 
activity in spite of the guarantee that the German Government 
has given adding that Ankara felt disappointment on the issue. 
Ataman said necessary initiations were made in Ankara, Bonn and 
Frankfurt on the issue. He said "we think Germany's decision to 
ban PKK should not be diluted and this terror organization 
should not be encouraged" adding that "we will be in close 
connection with the German officials." 
  During the demonstration, separatists carried a picture of 
the leader of PKK and pieces of clothes symbolizing colors of 
the separatist terrorist organization. 
  Turkey earlier expressed pleasure to see determination of 
Germany to extradite supporters of terrorists who violated 
German laws. 

</TEXT>

