<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "NATO: Italy on Russia in </F>
Partnership for Peace"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 23 -- As host to the upcoming G-7 
summit in Naples in July, Italy welcomes Russia's entry into the 
NATO Partnership for Peace program, applauding Russia's growing 
involvement in international cooperation and the government's 
efforts at internal reform, according to a statement by the 
foreign ministry on Thursday [23 June]. 
  The entry of Russia into the Partnership for Peace, the 
foreign ministry said, "constitutes an important contribution 
towards the establishment of a European security system based on 
cooperation and dialogue in a united Europe." 

