<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Conditions Troops to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Conditions Troops to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2406074594 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1548 GMT 23 
Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2406074594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Rwanda/Italy: Berlusconi on </F>
Conditions for Involvement"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 23 -- Prime Minister Silvio 
Berlusconi on Thursday [23 June] reiterated that Italy would 
join an international peace-keeping force in Rwanda "only on 
certain conditions," including United Nations involvement and an 
agreement between the warring sides. 
  "If these conditions do not exist," Berlusconi told 
reporters 
after a cabinet meeting, "Italy will intervene with humanitarian 
action outside Rwandan territory." 
  An Italian peace-keeping contingent in Rwanda would involve 
450 troops. 
  Defense Minister Cesare Previti said Italian collaboration 
with France, which plans to deploy an interposition force of 
2,000 troops, is possible only "within the limits of 
humanitarian and logistical contributions." 

</TEXT>

