<H3> <TI>   Ministries To Form Fact-Finding Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministries To Form Fact-Finding Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2706102794 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1449 GMT 25 
Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2706102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Rwanda: Italian Defense-Foreign </F>
Ministry Joint Mission"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 25 -- Italy early next week will 
send a joint delegation, from its foreign affairs and defense 
ministries, on a fact-finding mission to ascertain whether 
Italian troops could contribute to humanitarian efforts Rome has 
already embarked on there, a statement from the Foreign Ministry 
said. 
  The Farnesina [Foreign Ministry] added how the decision was 
made this morning during a defense-foreign coordination session 
and fell within "the framework of initiative by the Italian 
Government in favor of the populations in Rwanda and following 
the recent proposal to initiate consultations on a WEU (Western 
European Union) level and followed up by contacts the premier 
and foreign minister had in Corfu." 
  The ministry went on to state how this morning's session 
considered actions of protection and support of health 
structures, escorting convoys of prime necessities and refugees, 
as well as offering air transport. 

