<F P=106> [Article signed JWI: "No Belgian Military Personnel in </F>
Zaire Assures Brussels"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 27 Jun (BELGA) -- No Belgian military 
personnel will be sent to Zaire as part of the logistical aid 
which Belgium is prepared to give to France for its Operation 
Turquoise in Rwanda, said concordant government sources on 
Monday [27 June]. 
  On Monday afternoon, the defense minister did not rule out 
that "a few dozen men" who are part of a medical unit would be 
sent in a few days to western Rwanda. The minister had said in 
the morning that Paris had asked Belgium to give it logistical 
aid -- more specifically, a medical unit -- for its Operation 
Turquoise in Rwanda. 
  Another government source, however, indicated to BELGA that 
it was unlikely that a single Belgian soldier would be sent to 
Africa. In this case, Belgian aid will be limited to providing 
medical aid, but without any human presence whatsoever. 

</TEXT>

