<F P=106> [Report signed "SN, APA": "Protest Against Li Peng Visit"] </F>
  [Text] Vienna -- A number of human rights organizations 
protested on Friday [24 June] against the upcoming visit to 
Austria by Chinese Government head Li Peng. In an appeal that 
was signed by Amnesty International and Pax Christi, among 
others, the Federal Government is asked to discuss with the 
guest the serious human rights violations in China. Li Peng is 
responsible for the Tienanmen massacre five years ago, the 
appeal further notes. By hosting an official reception for Li 
Peng, the government is proving "how little it cares for human 
rights when it can expect profits." 

</TEXT>

