<H3> <TI>   Algerian Prime Minister Arrives in Rome </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Algerian Prime Minister Arrives in Rome </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806164494 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] In a second move towards the outside world, the 
prime minister, Mr Mokdad Sifi, embarks today on a European-Arab 
tour that will take him to Italy, Egypt, and Saudi Arabia. 
  He arrived this morning in the Italian capital, Rome, 
leading 
a ministerial delegation on an official one-day visit to Italy. 
  The head of government, accompanied by the finance, energy, 
and equipment, ministers, at noon today will confer with Italian 
President Mr Oscar Luigi Scalfaro. [passage omitted] 
  After Italy, stops in Cairo and Riyadh will enable Mr. Sifi 
to review the means to bolster cooperation between Algeria and 
Egypt on one hand and between Algeria and Saudi Arabia on the 
other. 
  He is carrying two message from Liamine Zeroual, the head of 
state, to both Egyptian President Husni Mubarak and to King Fahd 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz. 

</TEXT>

