<H3> <TI>   HURRIYET, MILLIYET Form Partnership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    HURRIYET, MILLIYET Form Partnership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2806192494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2806192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] A giant merger in the press world -- the dailies 
MILLIYET and HURRIYET became partners. 
  The Dogan Group which owns MILLIYET joined the Hurriyet 
Holding Company by buying 50 percent of its shares. The news, 
heard only this afternoon, created a great commotion in the 
press world. 
  In statements they issued this evening, the two dailies 
confirmed the partnership. They said that this merger will 
enable the two groups to make a major technological step. They 
said that the existing installations of the two groups inside 
Turkey will be joined, and new printing installations set up in 
certain places. They also pointed out that the partnership will 
enable them to extend a speedier and more modern newspaper 
service to their readers both technically and from the viewpoint 
of content. 

</TEXT>

