<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Algeria's Sifi Open to Dialogue With Moderates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Algeria's Sifi Open to Dialogue With Moderates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306224394 Paris Radio France International in French 2130 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306224394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Algerian Prime Minister Mokdad Sifi has finished his 
visit to Paris. After meeting President Francois Mitterrand 
yesterday, he held talks today with Foreign Minister Alain 
Juppe, who told him that France wants to see legislative 
elections organized in Algeria as soon as possible. 
  The prime minister held a news conference this afternoon, at 
the end of his two-day working visit. To those who ask his 
country to talk with the Islamists, he had this to say: 
  [Begin Sifi recording] I ask this of those who, far from the 
realities of the situation on the ground, advise us to 
negotiate: With whom? People tell us about the moderates all 
the time. There are many moderates in the National Transition 
Council. Who are the other moderates one hears about? Where 
are these moderates? Let them declare themselves, and let them 
condemn violence and terrorism. The doors of dialogue are wide 
open to them. Let them come. 
  President Zeroual and my government are in favor of dialogue 
with all those who first unequivocally and without rhetoric 
condemn violence and terrorism. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

