<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Martino, Kinkel Discuss EU Candidates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Martino, Kinkel Discuss EU Candidates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2906080294 Paris AFP in English 2206 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2906080294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Rome, June 28 (AFP) -- German Foreign Minister 
Klaus Kinkel said here Tuesday [28 June] that he hoped the 
dispute over a successor to Jacques Delors as European 
Commission president would be resolved before an emergency EU 
summit on July 15. 
  Kinkel, speaking after talks with Italian Foreign Minister 
Antonio Martino, said: "Clearly our goal is to find a solution 
before July 15." [passage omitted] 
  Kinkel said he and Martino had discussed other candidates 
but 
he refused to say which ones. 
  Kinkel said he would meet Wednesday in London with Major and 
Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd. "After that, we will see," he 
said. 

</TEXT>

