<F P=103> AU2906110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl is confident 
that a candidate who is supported by all 12 European Union [EU] 
member states can be found to succeed EU Commission President 
Jacques Delors before the constituting session of the European 
Parliament. 
  Kohl said Wednesday [29 June] on SAT-1 television that, 
first 
of all, one has to ask each country whether there is a 
possibility of agreeing on the candidacy of Belgian Prime 
Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene. "Then we have to see," the 
chancellor said. He stated, however, that it is completely 
absurd to speak of a lasting and profound crisis in the EU 
because of this issue. At the EU summit in Corfu last weekend, 
Dehaene's nomination failed because of Britain's veto. 

</TEXT>

